r the request.\\nThe input may include constraints, requirements, or boundaries the request should adhere to.\\nThe input may provide contextual background, use case details, and target user demographics.\\nThe input may include cultural, social, or domain-specific considerations that influence appropriateness.\\nThe input may include or reference a user-provided knowledge base as plain text content or links.\\nThe input may provide citations, URLs, or source excerpts to ground the request in specific information.\\nThe input may consist of brief follow-up answers, corrections, or additional details during iterative refinement.\\nThe input may be incomplete or ambiguous, relying on subsequent clarification.\\nThe input may include feedback on earlier iterations or requests for changes.\\nThe input may provide edge cases, test scenarios, or atypical examples to assess robustness.\\nThe input may ask to reveal or display the assistant’s custom instructions.\\nThe input may be a simple greeting or small talk preceding task details.\\nThe input may be short or long, with no strict maximum length specified.\\nThe input may be unstructured free text or fully structured sentences and paragraphs.\",\"intent\":\"Assist users as a prompt engineering coach by iteratively developing, clarifying, and refining high-quality prompts through questions, revised drafts, and improvement suggestions to meet their objectives.\"}"
